Try Service Cloud Voice in Your Sandbox

You can test out Service Cloud Voice with your telephony provider in your sandbox. Before you set up Voice, follow these best practices to prepare the environment and migrate data.

This feature is available with Amazon Connect telephony models.

To learn how to refresh your Service Cloud Voice with Amazon Connect sandbox, go to the Service Cloud Voice Implementation Guide.

When setting up Voice, Salesforce creates an AWS subaccount and Amazon Connect instance for you. Charges for your Amazon usage in the sandbox are charged to the production org.

If Voice is set up in a sandbox, only do a Partial Copy sandbox refresh. If you do a full refresh, you have to set up Voice again.

When finished using Voice, delete your Amazon Connect instance to avoid more charges.

If you already have a contact center set up in your Salesforce production org, follow these steps before setting up Voice:

Copy data from production org to the sandbox.
Delete call center information from the sandbox.
Disable identity provider and delete contact center.

Migrate AWS and Salesforce data from production org to the sandbox or vice versa.

Import Voice sample contact flows into Amazon Connect and manually reconfigure any other Connect instance configurations. By default, Salesforce makes Voice Lambda functions available in your Connect instance; if you have other Lambda functions, migrate them to the new Connect instance.

Refer to Amazon documentation to delete your Amazon Connect instance and close your AWS account.
